This is normal and expected, the go template works of the source code field names and not the json/yaml field names. As such the fields are generally always upper case as go generally uses PascalCase as naming convention.

I don't know what key you mean in podman inspect they also use upper case fields, you even can use shell completion to list them
```
podman inspect --format {{.
{{.AppArmorProfile}}          {{.EffectiveCaps}}            {{.ImageDigest}}              {{.Name}}                     {{.ProcessLabel}}
{{.Args}}                     {{.ExecIDs}}                  {{.ImageName}}                {{.Namespace}}                {{.ResolvConfPath}}
{{.BoundingCaps}}             {{.GraphDriver.               {{.IsInfra}}                  {{.NetworkSettings.           {{.RestartCount}}
{{.Config.                    {{.HostConfig.                {{.IsService}}                {{.OCIConfigPath}}            {{.Rootfs}}
{{.ConmonPidFile}}            {{.HostnamePath}}             {{.KubeExitCodePropagation}}  {{.OCIRuntime}}               {{.SizeRootFs}}
{{.Created.                   {{.HostsPath}}                {{.LockNumber}}               {{.Path}}                     {{.SizeRw}}
{{.Dependencies}}             {{.ID}}                       {{.MountLabel}}               {{.PidFile}}                  {{.State.
{{.Driver}}                   {{.Image}}                    {{.Mounts}}                   {{.Pod}}                      {{.StaticDir}}
```
